Begin forwarded message:

&gt; From: Kenichi Hatakeyama &lt;kenichi.hatakeyama@cern.ch&gt;
&gt; Date: October 28, 2011 3:20:11 AM GMT+02:00
&gt; To: &lt;hn-cms-met@cern.ch&gt;
&gt; Subject: MET systematic uncertainty tool
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; *** Discussion title: JetMET: Missing ET
&gt; 
&gt; Dear MET enthusiasts,
&gt; 
&gt; Although we had this twiki:
&gt; https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMS/MissingETUncertaintyPrescription
&gt; for the MET uncertainties, we did not have a standard code to evaluate
&gt; the MET uncertainties, and there have been many requests to provide this.
&gt; Many thanks to *Christian Veelken* and others, the first version of the
&gt; MET uncertainty evaluation code is now available in the PAT framework.
&gt; 
&gt; The technical details on the usage of this code are written on this twiki:
&gt; https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMSPublic/SWGuidePATTools#MET_Systematics_Tools 
&gt; 
&gt; The necessary package tags are on:
&gt; https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMSPublic/WorkBookMetAnalysis#HeadingFive 
&gt; 
&gt; Regarding what this code does, see e.g.Christian Veelken - Oct 27 - MET 
&gt; meeting - page 18-21
&gt; https://indico.cern.ch/contributionDisplay.py?contribId=5&confId=159994
&gt; 
&gt; The systematic variations of various objects still need to be finalized,
&gt; and we are working on it. In the meantime, it will be great if people
&gt; can start trying this and give feedback to the developers and us.
&gt; 
&gt; Best Regards,
&gt; Christian, Artur, Sarah, and Ken
&gt; 
