Begin forwarded message:

&gt; From: Christian Veelken &lt;christian.veelken@cern.ch&gt;
&gt; Date: January 4, 2012 4:55:29 PM GMT+01:00
&gt; To: &lt;hn-cms-tauid@cern.ch&gt;
&gt; Subject: AN-11/514: tau id. efficiency measurement in 2011 run B data
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; *** Discussion title: Tau ID
&gt; 
&gt; Dear all,
&gt; 
&gt; documentation of the tau id. efficiency measurement in 2011 run B data is available in an Analysis Note now.
&gt; The link to the latest version is
&gt;   http://cms.cern.ch/iCMS/jsp/openfile.jsp?tp=draft&files=AN2011_514_v2.pdf
&gt; 
&gt; The main results are:
&gt; (1) the tau id. efficiency efficiency measured in 2011 run B data is compatible with the MC expectation within uncertainties
&gt; (2) the combined statistical + systematic uncertainty is about 6% for run A and for run B data
&gt; (3) there is no indication that the MC would not model the pile-up dependence of the tau id. efficiency well
&gt;       (the pile-up dependence is quite sizeable for the "classic" HPS medium and tight isolation discriminators with no delta-beta corrections applied)
&gt; 
&gt; Happy reading (and happy new year :o),
&gt; cheers,
&gt; 
&gt; Christian
&gt; 
&gt; -------------------------------------------------------------
&gt; Visit this CMS message (to reply or unsubscribe) at: 
&gt; https://hypernews.cern.ch/HyperNews/CMS/get/tauid/204.html

