Begin forwarded message:

&gt; From: "Evan K. Friis" &lt;Evan.Klose.Friis@cern.ch&gt;
&gt; Date: January 13, 2012 3:27:58 PM GMT+01:00
&gt; To: &lt;hn-cms-tauid@cern.ch&gt;
&gt; Subject: Update to anti-electron MVA discriminator
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; *** Discussion title: Tau ID
&gt; 
&gt; Dear all,
&gt; 
&gt; We have recently discovered an inconsistency in the implementation of the
&gt; MVA electron rejection discriminator.  (from here [1])
&gt; 
&gt; The MVA was trained using tau candidates which pass the
&gt; AgainstElectronMedium discriminator, so it should only be used on
&gt; candidates which pass AgainstMedium.
&gt; 
&gt; I believe most analysis groups are doing this already (taking the AND of
&gt; both discriminators).  If not, we recommend that you do so.  As of the tag
&gt; V01-02-12 of RecoTauTag/Configuration (added on [1] today), this will be
&gt; done automatically.
&gt; 
&gt; Cheers,
&gt; 
&gt; Evan
&gt; 
&gt; [1]
&gt; https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMSPublic/SWGuidePFTauID#Beta_Electron_Rejection_MVA
&gt; 
