&gt;&gt; ·         Statuses
&gt;&gt; Following input from participants, there will now be 2 statuses for the results of work or supervisory objectives: 
&gt;&gt; “Achieved or partially achieved” and “Suppressed or not achieved”.  For the status “Achieved or partially achieved” at least one competency must be indicated.  For the status “Suppressed or not achieved” the indication of a competency is optional.
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; ·         Health & Safety
&gt;&gt; Under Section 4 of the MARS form (Health and Safety), a checkbox has been added to indicate that the occupational hazards questionnaire has been completed.  More detailed information on this subject will be sent in January by the HSE Unit and the Medical Service.  The EDH team is currently working on an EDH version of this form, but for the 2012 MARS exercise it will be necessary to complete a Word document, available via EDMS, that will be signed on paper and sent to the Medical Service for their records.
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; ·         Training requests
&gt;&gt; We should like to clarify that the Training Catalogue list of training courses available at CERN (CTA catalogue) is still available in the MARS form for information.  However, the generation of training requests from the MARS form will no longer be automatic as from 2012.  The supervisor or staff member should generate the training request in EDH separately, if an internal or external training course is selected as a development objective. 
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; Finally, we should like to clarify the responsibilities of the supervisor as regards completing the MARS form.  During the editing phase of the document, the supervisor and staff member both have the possibility of editing the results of work objectives fields.  However, it is ultimately the responsibility of the supervisor to ensure the information reflects his/her analysis of the results of each objective.  It is also ultimately the supervisor who should select the relevant competencies which best reflect these results.
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; With best regards,
&gt;&gt; Sara Stappers
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; HR Department
&gt;&gt; MARS Coordination Team
&gt;

