&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; in the context of our analysis of H-&gt;ZZ-2l2j, we perform the cleaning of the jets from the collections of isolated leptons.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; This cleaning is done by adding a flag to the jets themselves, basically saying "this jet was matched to a lepton".
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; then we filter the jets if the flag is active or not.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Similarly, we do a matching to the parton level looping on the status==3 GenParticles and again activating some flag.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; This is important for studies on the signal shape because we have signal events that are reconstructed picking the 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; "wrong" jet (not matched to parton level).
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; All of this was done with pat::Jets with the stabdard PATMatcher (a simple DeltaR matching). 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Now we are migrating to the CMG framework and we need to have this working with cmgJet and the collections
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; in the CMG-PATtuples. I was going to start to write a module doing this when I found this other written by you
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; http://cmssw.cvs.cern.ch/cgi-bin/cmssw.cgi/UserCode/CMG/CMGTools/Common/plugins/DeltaRVetoProducer.cc?view=log
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; http://cmssw.cvs.cern.ch/cgi-bin/cmssw.cgi/UserCode/CMG/CMGTools/Common/python/miscProducers/deltaRJetElectrons_cfi.py?revision=1.2&view=markup
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; It does mostly what we need, it should work also on a veto collection of GenParticle (they inherit from reco::Candidate), 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; if not that it's missing to flag the cmgJet. This could be done by adding one more strbitset to the jet
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; jet.addSelection("matchedToLepton", isMatched);
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; and adding the possibility to the Producer to store all the jets even if they were matched to some input to the vetoCollection.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Does it make sense ? Is it fine if I implement these changes in the code, I test them, we look at them (mainly for the code style)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; and commit them ? I can also pass by your office if you want to talk about this more in detail.
