&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; I am running a test now using the == operator for the duplicate removal just to see what the difference is. I see the == operator is defined as p4()=other.p4() and charge()==other.charge().
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; However, I think we should avoid any further problems by not applying the duplicate removal at all. I was concerned with removing duplicates only because of the additional duplication which appears to be done inside the TriggerObjectFactory, however in the new algorithm this additional duplication is not done. Removing the duplicates which are inherent in the input HLT collection has a really small impact on the ntuple size: 103641134 bytes  --&gt; 103011716 bytes for 20k events. The increase in size comes from saving all the filter labels.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Hmm, Ok. I guess the saving will be pretty small. You plan to completely drop the ability to use these collections interactively? If so, perhaps we should go back to just keeping the collection of pat::triggerObjectStandAlone or whatever they are called?
