Begin forwarded message:

&gt; From: Andrzej Zuranski &lt;zuranski@princeton.edu&gt;
&gt; Date: October 30, 2011 5:23:32 PM GMT+01:00
&gt; To: &lt;hn-cms-commissioning@cern.ch&gt;
&gt; Subject: Proton Run of 2011 Completed!
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; *** Discussion title: CMS Commissioning
&gt; 
&gt; Dear Collaborators,
&gt; 
&gt; at 17:00 today the LHC dumped the last proton beams
&gt; for the year to start the machine development period
&gt; and to prepare for the ion running. This means that we have
&gt; come to the end of the proton operation for 2011.
&gt; 
&gt; In 2011 the LHC delivered 5.74 fb-1 and CMS has
&gt; recorded 5.21 fb-1. Statistics about the data recorded
&gt; in 2011 can be found at:
&gt; 
&gt; https://cmswbm.web.cern.ch/cmswbm/cmsdb/servlet/DataSummary?SUBMIT=yearly
&gt; 
&gt; A few highlights from the run this year:
&gt; 
&gt; Peak Instantaneous Luminosity: 3.55Ã-1033 Hz/cm2 in fill 2256 2011.10.26
&gt; Delivered luminosity in one Fill: 123 pb-1 in fill 2219    2011.10.16
&gt; Maximum Luminosity in one Day: 136 pb-1 on 2011.10.13
&gt; Maximum Luminosity Delivered in one Week: 538 pb-1 in week 41
&gt; Maximum Luminosity Delivered in one Month: 1614 pb-1 in October
&gt; 
&gt; The LHC were in stable beams 1364 hours this year.
&gt; 
&gt;  Anders/Maria/Luca/Andrzej/Christoph 
&gt; 
&gt; -------------------------------------------------------------
&gt; Visit this CMS message (to reply or unsubscribe) at: 
&gt; https://hypernews.cern.ch/HyperNews/CMS/get/commissioning/3607.html

