&gt; CommonTools/ParticleFlow   B4_2_X_V00-03-00
&gt; I will run a customIB and publish the corresponding AT tags with it for future 42X releases. 
&gt; 
&gt; Cheers,
&gt; Roger
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Hi Roger, 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; The back-port is ready. 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; I started from the current 4_2_X tag set 
&gt;&gt; https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMSPublic/SWGuidePATReleaseNotes42X#V08_06_42
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; The new tag set I propose is : 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Test Release based on: CMSSW_4_2_8
&gt;&gt; Base Release in: /afs/cern.ch/cms/slc5_amd64_gcc434/cms/cmssw/CMSSW_4_2_8
&gt;&gt; Your Test release in: /data/c/cbern/ParticleFlow/BackPortIso/TestBackPort/CMSSW_4_2_8
&gt;&gt; --- Tag ---    -------- Package --------                        
&gt;&gt; B4_2_X_V00-03-00 CommonTools/ParticleFlow                         
&gt;&gt; cbern_isolation_V06-04-19-01 DataFormats/PatCandidates                        
&gt;&gt; B4_2_X_cbern_isolation_29Sept11_d PhysicsTools/PatAlgos                            
&gt;&gt; V00-05-24      PhysicsTools/PatExamples                         
&gt;&gt; V00-03-24      PhysicsTools/SelectorUtils                       
&gt;&gt; V08-02-14      PhysicsTools/UtilAlgos                           
&gt;&gt; ---------------------------------------
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Basically: 
&gt;&gt; - I took the B4_2_X tip for PhysicsTools/PatAlgos, which contains my back-ported modifications.
&gt;&gt; - For DataFormats/PatCandidates, I took the tag V06-04-19-01 from the last recipe, and just updated Isolation.h and Lepton.h before tagging.
&gt;&gt; - I had to use the B4_2_X branch for CommonTools/ParticleFlow for two reasons: 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;               - the isolation definition from RecoMuon/MuonIsolation is not there in 4_2_X, so I had to put these files in CommonTools/ParticleFlow for the back port.
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;               - the obsolete files TJ wanted me to remove are needed in PhysicsTools/PatAlgos, because of the famos bootstrap. I decided to put these files back in the 4_2_X branch, instead of messing with that. This choice allows me not to include additional reco packages in the back port.  
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; I tested that the muon isolation behaves as expected, with and without the delta beta correction (see below). 
&gt;&gt; The delta beta correction is disabled by default in the PF2PAT cross-cleaning, but can of course be applied after the fact using the pat::Muon. 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Please let me know if you need more information, or if you see any problem with this recipe. 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Cheers, 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Colin
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Isolation as a function of the number of vertices: flat when dbeta corrections are applied
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Combined isolation, with and without the dbeta correction.
&gt;&gt; The cut at 0.15 in PF2PAT is visible. It is clear that we're cutting on the isolation wich is NOT delta beta corrected: 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Isolation value for the various components.
&gt;&gt; I would be cutting on the dbeta corrected isolation in PF2PAT (which is not the case), 
&gt;&gt; the photon and neutral hadron isolation would extend further than 0.15, 
&gt;&gt; and the charged hadron isolation would still stop at 0.15. 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; 
