Dear Lucie,
I'm now on vacation, but will be able to send you the title and abstract on Monday next week. Btw, I would like to meet you on Monday if possible to tell you about the situation of the particle flow in CMS, because I'm not really sure that having this seminar now is the best solution (briefly: the CMS collaboration did nothing to validate the particle flow in 2011, and I will have to present rather old results from 2010).
The various documents you might want to cite in the CLIC CDR are :
Description of the particle flow algorithm:
@ARTICLE{PFT-09-001, COLLABORATION= "CMS", TITLE = "Particle-Flow Event Reconstruction in CMS and Performance for Jets, Taus, and Missing $E_{\rm T}$", JOURNAL = "CMS PAS", VOLUME = "\href{http://cms-physics.web.cern.ch/cms-physics/public/PFT-09-001-pas.pdf}{PFT-09-001}", YEAR = "2009"}
Validation of the particle flow reconstruction of photons, charged hadrons, and neutral hadrons, and of particle flow jets and MET:
@ARTICLE{PFT-10-002, COLLABORATION= "CMS", TITLE = "Commissioning of the Particle-Flow Reconstruction in Minimum-Bias and Jet Events from pp Collisions at 7 TeV", JOURNAL = "CMS PAS", VOLUME = "\href{http://cms-physics.web.cern.ch/cms-physics/public/PFT-10-002-pas.pdf}{PFT-10-002}", YEAR = "2010"}
Validation of the particle flow electron and muon reconstruction:
@ARTICLE{PFT-10-003, COLLABORATION= "CMS", TITLE = "Commissioning of the particle-flow event reconstruction with leptons from J/Psi and W decays at 7 TeV", JOURNAL = "CMS PAS", VOLUME = "\href{http://cms-physics.web.cern.ch/cms-physics/public/PFT-10-003-pas.pdf}{PFT-10-003}", YEAR = "2010"}
Cheers,
Colin
