&gt; Begin forwarded message:
&gt; 
&gt;&gt; From: Nathalie Knoors &lt;Nathalie.Knoors@cern.ch&gt;
&gt;&gt; Subject: MARS 2012 preparation & latest news
&gt;&gt; Date: December 16, 2011 12:55:31 PM GMT+01:00
&gt;&gt; To: "ph-dep-group-leaders (group leaders of PH department)" &lt;ph-dep-group-leaders@cern.ch&gt;
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt; Dear all,
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; Please find below a summary of the this year’s changes to the EDH MARS document, information on MARS and the CCM training. The new model will mainly affect the discussion during the MARS interviews of the Work and Development objectives for the next period of reference. The new e-MARS form will be available beginning of January and a review of all the MARS FAQ will be processed before the end of January.
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; The key dates for the MARS 2012 are available at https://admin-eguide.web.cern.ch/admin-eguide/mars/mars.asp .
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; A new version of the administrative circular “Recognition of Merit” n.26 has been approved by the DG and will be available soon ; the main changes are the financial awards and more particularly the awards for extraordinary service :
&gt;&gt;                 . Individual amount of a minimum of 500 CHF and a maximum of 5000 CHF for teamwork (minimum 2 persons) ;
&gt;&gt;                 . Individual amount of a minimum of 1000 CHF and maximum of 5000 CHF for individual work.
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; A.      e-MARS EDH report integration of CCM
&gt;&gt; a)      Workflow changes
&gt;&gt; Involvement of current hierarchy only , 2 steps have been removed :
&gt;&gt;         . Previous supervisor signature,
&gt;&gt;         . Previous Group Leader signature,
&gt;&gt; 1 more step has been removed :
&gt;&gt;         . Removal of automated training requests : - further information on the implications of this decision will be communicated in due course -
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; b)      Work and supervisory results
&gt;&gt; For each result of a fixed objective, identify related technical and/or behavioral competency :
&gt;&gt;         . 1 competency is mandatory
&gt;&gt;         . Not possible to have 2 technical or 2 behavioral competencies per objective, should be maximum one of each             
&gt;&gt; For each result obtained, select one of the 2 status :
&gt;&gt;         . Achieved or partially achieved : this implies that the indication of 1 related competency is mandatory and two maximum can be selected (1 Technical and/or 1 Behavioral) with concrete example(s) allowing                         interpretation of context (demonstrated or not)
&gt;&gt;         . Suppressed or not achieved : this implies that competencies are optional          
&gt;&gt; Evaluation of results over the reference period :
&gt;&gt;         . Results obtained = What is Achieved ?
&gt;&gt;         . Concrete example = How are the results achieved ? The example is strictly related to the selected competency ; the purpose of providing an example helps identify the competency needed  and allows a narrative      qualification related to the selected competency.
&gt;&gt; c)       Development objectives
&gt;&gt;         . Automatic generation of training requests abolished - further information on the implications of this decision will be communicated in due course -
&gt;&gt;                 . The list of activity proposed includes CERN Internal Training, Other Training Course, On-the-job Training, Shadowing, Self Study, Other Activity
&gt;&gt;                 . The details field allows to be more specific on the selected activity
&gt;&gt;                 . Indication of one competency – technical or behavioral – per objective to be developed
&gt;&gt;                 . No restrictions on the number of development objectives
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; d)      Health and Safety Check
&gt;&gt;                 . “Identification of occupational hazards” questionnaire accessible from the e-MARS form to be completed and signed by the supervisor and the staff member, and send to the Medical Service.
&gt;&gt;                 . An automatic transfer of this questionnaire to the Medical Service via EDH will be studied and developed at a later stage by the AIS team.
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; B.      CCM Training and MARS
&gt;&gt; a)      CCM in MARS : Making the most of the annual MARS interview at CERN – Competency-based Performance Appraisal Workshop  for Supervisees
&gt;&gt;         .  Hands-on workshop to demonstrate how to relate competencies and objectives, including a presentation of the new MARS form
&gt;&gt; . STAFF sessions of 3 hours organized until end of January, beginning of February
&gt;&gt; . Highly recommended
&gt;&gt; . Pre-requisite : Attended the CCM training module - Understanding and working with Competencies
&gt;&gt; . Registration at https://hr-training.web.cern.ch/hr-training/ if staff members did not participate yet and preferably before their next MARS interview!
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; b)      CCM in MARS for Supervisors
&gt;&gt;         . All supervisors to have followed training by mid-February 2012
&gt;&gt;         . Please send me the names of new MARS supervisors if any as soon as possible
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; More information is available at https://cern.ch/hr-info/competencies.asp
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt; Best wishes, Nathalie
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt;  
&gt;&gt;  
